RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 1 300 Y Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Purse 7300. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VALS CORONADO bumped, erratic, all out. TRUMMPY late surge. DIEGO VALENTINO drifted out, bothered foes. EL GATO MEXICANO bumped, erratic trip. BRAVE PANTHER DG hopped start, late gain. FANCY FAMOUS JEANS steadied late. THEPARTYISOVERHERE unruly behind gate, steadied late. XO GRACE foe crossed path. STREAKIN WITH STOLI not involved. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS POSTED ALONG WITH A JOCKEY OBJECTION, THE JOCKEY OF FANCY FAMOUS JEANS CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE JOCKEY OF DIEGO VALENTINO FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE NEAR THE WIRE. AFTER A STEWARD REVIEW THE CLAIM OF FOUL WAS DISALLOWED BUT THE STEWARD TOOK ACTION ON DIEGO VALENTINO AND DISQUALIFIED HIM FROM THIRD TO SEVENTH FOR INTERFERENCE NEAR THE WIRE.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 75. Allowance Purse 12100. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD NON WINNERS OF TWO RACES LIFETIME OR COLORADO BRED NON WINNERS OF THREE RACES LIFETIME. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRACIE'S A TIGER pressed the pace to the top of the stretch from the two path, drifted in slightly near the eighth pole, rubbed inside rival but kept on and drew clear. HIGH GUNNER chased the top two around the turn and made a late gain. BAKERSFIELD BABE went to the front to a pressured lead from the inside to the top of the stretch then drifted out, rubbed the outside rival near the eighth pole and tired. LOTTA PRADA raced in the middle of the pace to the turn then moved up the rail around the turn but faltered. MAKARA tracked the leaders from the middle of the pace but was not a factor. WON SASSY RIDE was fractious in the gate and unseated rider, trailed early and was not a threat. NOBLE PRESENT was not a threat. A TRAINER OBJECTION WAS POSTED, THE TRAINER OF BAKERSFIELD BABE CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST GRACIE'S A TIGER FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE AT THE EIGHTH POLE, AFTER A STEWARDS REVIEW THE CLAIM OF FOUL WAS DISALLOWED AND NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: EXTRA SAUCE sprinted away from the gate, prompted the pace on the backstretch then moved to engage the leader at the three furlong marker and took the lead at the quarter pole, cleared late. TEQUILA RITA raced near the back to mid turn then moved up from between horses at the quarter pole but was outfinished in the stretch. RETRO RITA was off the pace from three wide to the top of the stretch and weakened. PASSION RIDE saved ground while moving up around the turn but faltered. GOSPEL FAITH hopped at the start and trailed through the turn but was not a threat. WEST COAST ANDY raced in the middle of the pack to mid turn and retreated.
